name: Seeing is not Believing
description: A digitally programmed art piece. Two sets of triangles are arranged evenly throughout the canvas. Left half red, right half blue, with a solid purple background.   However the background appears to be two different colors. With red triangles in the foreground, the background appears to have a more purple hue and vise versa with the blue triangles. The eye darts around the page as it follows the triangles pattern.The way our minds interpret reality, may not be an accurate representation of what the external world actually is. In this scenario one cannot see it to believe. one must believe it to see it.
